Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.11,0:00:05.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did you not hear me? I said to let me pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.91,0:00:08.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have no business with you, Assassin.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.37,0:00:11.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And did you not hear me when I \Nsaid to force your way through?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.37,0:00:16.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you do not hurry, your Master's life will be lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.59,0:00:20.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so angry at Assassin, Caster.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.13,0:00:23.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He faces Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.30,0:00:25.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know who that samurai is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.92,0:00:29.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but to hold Saber at bay, he is \Na master swordsman indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.18,0:00:31.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't you be complimenting him instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.44,0:00:34.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you jest.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.44,0:00:38.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I should hardly call him a hero if \Nhe failed to stop the likes of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.69,0:00:43.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That man lacks the skills to make a master \Nswordsman reveal their name.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.20,0:00:45.37,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Saber is here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.15,0:02:20.75,Title,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(279,277)}#07 The Reward for the Fight to the Death
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.05,0:02:31.97,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How can this be?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.64,0:02:37.01,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Weight, power, speed... I have \Nthe advantage in all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.39,0:02:39.13,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why can I not break his defense?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.78,0:02:48.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.74,0:02:53.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I should have taken your head seven \Ntimes, but it remains attached.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.08,0:02:56.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It appears Western swordplay is \Nmore than mere flailing, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.29,0:02:59.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And you, as well. For a man of such slight build, \Nyour technique is impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.87,0:03:01.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If nothing else, you are skilled in trickery.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.96,0:03:05.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. You have the edge in \Nboth strength and spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.55,0:03:08.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That leaves me only my wiles to defeat you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.80,0:03:12.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have nearly adjusted to your \Ninvisible sword, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.14,0:03:15.06,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just from that brief exchange?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.06,0:03:19.39,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Does this Servant surpass me so \Ngreatly in sword technique?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.39,0:03:21.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let us continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.15,0:03:23.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Show me what you are really capable of, Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.32,0:03:27.53,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou... Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.90,0:03:35.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,From what you've said, your Masters work together?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.24,0:03:37.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Work together?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.08,0:03:38.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.06,0:03:42.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Assassin guards the gate, \Nand Caster lurks within.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.71,0:03:45.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it obvious these two are allied?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.84,0:03:48.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't particularly unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.26,0:03:51.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For example, you and Rin have joined forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.31,0:04:00.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Me? Work with that dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.73,0:04:03.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With Assassin, who is no more than my pawn?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.86,0:04:04.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your pawn?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.27,0:04:06.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.40,0:04:10.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That dog has no Master, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.40,0:04:11.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.24,0:04:12.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Caster,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.36,0:04:14.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you broke the rules!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.78,0:04:20.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with a mage such as \Nmyself summoning a Servant?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.00,0:04:23.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Caster summoned Assassin?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.17,0:04:28.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying that a Servant \Nsummoned another Servant?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.09,0:04:33.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That gatekeeper there, not summoned by \Na proper Master, is not the true Assassin.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.22,0:04:38.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She broke the rules and summoned an \NAssassin-class Servant by herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.89,0:04:43.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Establishing this as her territory, she harvests \Nsouls from people in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.31,0:04:44.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She herself doesn't fight,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.90,0:04:48.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but monitors the battle with borrowed \Neyes throughout the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.61,0:04:52.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The three knight classes, which include \NSaber, aren't as affected by magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.53,0:04:57.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's only natural for a magic-user class such\Nas yourself to resort to underhanded tactics.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.24,0:05:01.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But was it not your own volition to do so, Caster?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.29,0:05:04.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What makes you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.04,0:05:07.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Masters and mages.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.04,0:05:10.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If one summons a mage more powerful than oneself,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.34,0:05:12.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,one would be on guard, even with Command Seals.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.67,0:05:14.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Given that,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.01,0:05:18.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it's hard to believe a Master would let \Nyou summon a Servant to obey you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.60,0:05:19.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In which case,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.10,0:05:25.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can imagine you've long since made a puppet \Nof him, like this fool of a Master behind me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.90,0:05:30.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Winning the Holy Grail War \Nwould be a simple matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.44,0:05:34.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My considerable effort is directed \Ntoward what comes after.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.90,0:05:38.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, defeating us is simple, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.74,0:05:42.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This from a witch, who does nothing \Nbut slink in the shadows?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.37,0:05:48.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, in this place, you may not \Nso much as scratch me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.96,0:05:51.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To those who call me a witch,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.13,0:05:53.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shall deal the appropriate punishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.84,0:05:56.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not even a scratch, you claim?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.34,0:05:59.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,One blow, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.76,0:06:03.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If that will not suffice, I will leave you to Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.37,0:06:23.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Too bad, Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.46,0:06:37.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Spatial Transportation? Innate Time Control?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.93,0:06:41.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Within this territory, you can mimic True Magic?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.35,0:06:45.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You impress me, Caster.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.35,0:06:49.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And you disappoint me, Archer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.48,0:06:53.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I tested you, thinking you might be useful, \Nbut you are worse than Assassin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.69,0:06:55.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.61,0:06:59.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I get another chance, I'll try \Nharder not to let you down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.75,0:07:17.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You vixen... You have a huge store \Nof mana to draw on, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.35,0:07:27.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You think you can escape?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.86,0:07:35.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That imbecile!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.48,0:07:36.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.37,0:07:47.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Put me down, idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.70,0:07:49.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you thinking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.36,0:07:51.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The hell if I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.83,0:07:56.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,When you say that, your excessive \Nstupidity hurts my head! Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.13,0:07:57.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.62,0:08:02.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You know you're an idiot, and you go \Naround calling others idiots? Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.26,0:08:05.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What are you, a child?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.22,0:08:07.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can no longer tolerate a child and fool like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.81,0:08:10.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At least decide on one, numbskull!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.44,0:08:11.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.98,0:08:20.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Put me down, damn it!\NI can handle this myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.24,0:08:21.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can you, now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.08,0:08:26.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You son of a...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.79,0:08:32.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How does that feel, Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.21,0:08:38.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even the three knight classes cannot \Nmove if space itself is immobilized.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.26,0:08:42.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This would appear to be checkmate.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.68,0:08:46.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know which land's hero \Nyou were, but this is farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.77,0:08:54.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What was that, Archer? If you wish \Nto beg for your life, I can—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.23,0:08:57.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Imbecile! I said, "Dodge this," Caster!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.04,0:09:09.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.13,0:09:18.29,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am the bone of my sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.51,0:09:22.51,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Caladbolg!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.39,0:09:37.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that matters do not \Nprogress as planned up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.06,0:09:41.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My Master is in peril, so I no longer have \Nthe luxury of concealing my true skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.03,0:09:45.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even now, you will not reveal your Noble Phantasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.24,0:09:50.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your Master is unskilled, so you count \Non the strength of his luck?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.33,0:09:53.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your trust in him is admirable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.46,0:09:57.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see that halfhearted measures cannot break it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.04,0:09:59.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, that simply will not do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.88,0:10:03.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You yield the advantage of higher \Nground? What are you playing at?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.72,0:10:07.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I may have no true name, but I have \Ndevoted my life to the sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.16,0:10:09.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If giving all for this fight is not an option,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.35,0:10:13.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,shall I break open that belief with brute force?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.14,0:10:17.15,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Concealed Sword!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.07,0:10:23.01,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Swallow Reversal!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.19,0:10:23.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Too late!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.92,0:10:43.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer, why do you not finish me off?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.13,0:10:47.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I said I would test you with \Na single blow, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.64,0:10:53.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You do not intend to kill me, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.93,0:10:57.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My objective was this boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.44,0:11:00.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My policy is to avoid unnecessary fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.84,0:11:01.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.47,0:11:05.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.74,0:11:09.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You two are quite alike, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.95,0:11:16.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That boy cannot abide a Servant like me, \Nwho feeds on the innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.83,0:11:19.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And you dislike senseless slaughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.79,0:11:22.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,See? You are completely the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.17,0:11:24.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How am I anything like this jerk?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.96,0:11:25.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.21,0:11:30.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I admit we may both be pacifists, \Nbut for different reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.18,0:11:31.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You call yourself a pacifist?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.18,0:11:36.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't forgotten. You tried to destroy \NSaber along with Berserker!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.22,0:11:38.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That was before we entered into an alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.39,0:11:43.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you don't expect me \Nto save everything in sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.61,0:11:48.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thinking that way, even Berserker would \Nbe something to save, not defeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.57,0:11:53.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I like you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.03,0:11:56.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your strengths and the ways \Nyou use them are unique.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.16,0:11:59.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Join forces with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.33,0:12:02.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have a means to put an end to this war.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.71,0:12:03.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Never!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.79,0:12:06.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I won't work with people like you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.67,0:12:10.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it, Archer! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.68,0:12:12.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.18,0:12:15.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your team has limited fighting potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.43,0:12:19.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how much power you gain,\Nyou are no match for Berserker.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.60,0:12:22.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What you offer isn't enough\Nto ally myself with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.56,0:12:25.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Negotiations have\Nbroken down, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.98,0:12:30.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Correct. Besides, I've come \Nhere of my own volition.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.95,0:12:34.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My Master did not send me, so I \Nhave no reason to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.78,0:12:37.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we call this a draw due to injury?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.33,0:12:38.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.50,0:12:39.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.70,0:12:42.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your Master has been hunting me, has she not?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.96,0:12:45.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But still, you would let me go?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.88,0:12:51.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it is no concern of mine \Nhow many you kill here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.68,0:12:54.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What a terrible man you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.68,0:12:57.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute, Caster!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.94,0:13:09.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer, why did you let Caster go?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.36,0:13:14.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I'd struck her down, she'd have \Nsimply made her escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.07,0:13:18.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To defeat Caster,\Nwe must get to her Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.45,0:13:23.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But all the problems happening in town are her doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.54,0:13:26.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Until we stop her, victims will keep piling up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.04,0:13:30.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,On the contrary,\NI want to let her continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.88,0:13:37.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Caster will keep draining people of life force, \Nand will use that power to defeat Berserker.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.47,0:13:40.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We'll deal with Caster afterward.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.72,0:13:42.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka would never agree to such a plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.98,0:13:48.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're right, which is why I'd like Caster \Nto settle matters as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.61,0:13:53.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how many will die, \Nbut humans are mortal, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.74,0:13:56.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However they die, and at whose \Nhands, the result is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.00,0:14:07.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You withstood my Concealed Sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.50,0:14:12.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is not all that special as tricks go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.51,0:14:17.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's simply something I mastered when \NI thought to slay a sparrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.30,0:14:21.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A flying swallow will not be caught by \Nmy sword, which is but a single line.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.89,0:14:25.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But with two or three lines, \Nmatters change somewhat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.94,0:14:28.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, swallows are swift little things.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.65,0:14:33.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To accomplish the feat, one must strike \Nrepeatedly within a single breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.36,0:14:35.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But that is beyond ordinary men's ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.82,0:14:41.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But unfortunately for you, \NI had nothing better to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.58,0:14:44.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mastery through endless repetition.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.12,0:14:47.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The next thing I knew, I had accomplished it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.38,0:14:51.96,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't right. "Strike repeatedly \Nwithin a single breath"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.96,0:14:53.83,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Those blows were simultaneous.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.21,0:14:57.51,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At that instant, three swords existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.51,0:14:59.05,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As difficult as it is to believe...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.05,0:15:02.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That was a dimensional-refraction phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.33,0:15:08.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A Servant who uses only sword skills to \Nachieve what a Noble Phantasm would...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.94,0:15:15.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Caster is a soft-hearted. She should have \Ntaken their lives while she had the chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.94,0:15:19.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If everyone in the city dies, \Nfighting would be easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.78,0:15:20.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.62,0:15:27.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we had an alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.58,0:15:29.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's a load of crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.12,0:15:31.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm nothing like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.17,0:15:36.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Like I'd ever sacrifice those around me\Nto achieve victory or a goal!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.34,0:15:40.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I feel the same way, Emiya Shirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.76,0:15:44.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it is impossible to save everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.14,0:15:49.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If Caster wins the Grail, the damage \Nwon't be limited to this city alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.23,0:15:52.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If we fail to win, the damage will be even greater.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.23,0:15:57.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, the only choice is \Nto sacrifice this city's people.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.57,0:16:02.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If that has the result of keeping the overall\Nlosses low, it's the same as your strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.24,0:16:07.44,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Saving one person means being \Nunable to save another.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.71,0:16:12.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You said you didn't want to involve \Ninnocent people, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.63,0:16:14.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then admit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.38,0:16:18.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you try to avoid killing anyone, \Nyou won't save anyone in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.64,0:16:25.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You plan to go after Caster?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.47,0:16:29.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To waste that life which I went through \Nall that trouble to save—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.52,0:16:29.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.77,0:16:33.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't want your help, even if you offered!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.73,0:16:35.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.02,0:16:37.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your dislike of me makes this easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.06,0:17:16.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.44,0:17:18.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Son of a...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.15,0:17:22.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Emiya Shirou, if you have \Nno will to fight, die here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.11,0:17:28.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fighting for others, but not yourself, \Nis nothing but hypocrisy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.37,0:17:32.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't victory that you want. It's peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.91,0:17:36.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even though there isn't any \Nsuch thing in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.84,0:17:39.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.17,0:17:43.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Farewell. Let your ideals drag you to your death.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.56,0:17:51.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.98,0:17:56.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That vixen... She retreated?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.65,0:17:58.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Saber...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.86,0:18:06.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Assassin, just now, why did \Nyou not strike me down?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.82,0:18:09.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was captivated, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.74,0:18:14.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You were attractive when we fought, but your \Nconcern for your Master is exquisite.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.91,0:18:16.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, you caught my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.46,0:18:22.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is enough for tonight. You may go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.13,0:18:25.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're letting us go?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.30,0:18:29.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am indeed. To find a worthy \Nopponent is a rare thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.22,0:18:32.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you are not in peak form, \Nit would be a waste to defeat you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.10,0:18:35.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Or would you consider this a debt, Saber?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.27,0:18:38.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, Sasaki Kojirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.94,0:18:41.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive my rudeness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.44,0:18:44.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You were truly an opponent \Nworthy of my full attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.15,0:18:48.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rest assured, I shall settle things with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.91,0:18:53.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Regardless of the outcome of \Nthe Holy Grail War. I swear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.50,0:19:03.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You stand in my way, samurai?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.30,0:19:05.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's my line.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.72,0:19:08.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I said they may leave, and you would interfere?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.97,0:19:11.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My duty is to guard this gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.68,0:19:14.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I permitted entry, but exiting is another matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.35,0:19:19.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your head lacks elegance, but I shall \Nsatisfy myself by claiming it tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.06,0:19:22.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You think you can fight me, lackey of Caster?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.98,0:19:24.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I could say the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.65,0:19:28.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I sent you to give the vixen a scare,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.36,0:19:31.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so imagine my disappointment to see \Nyou flee for your own well-being.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.75,0:19:40.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou, while he's distracted...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.88,0:19:42.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.23,0:21:23.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.48,0:21:26.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So Archer allowed Caster to escape?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.40,0:21:28.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.27,0:21:29.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That guy is the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.98,0:21:36.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If he's willing to exploit someone like her to win, he's no better than Caster.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.91,0:21:40.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you smiling like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.83,0:21:45.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it is rare to hear you speak ill of someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.75,0:21:50.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But you aren't angry at Archer for attacking you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.05,0:21:58.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm allied with Tohsaka. Not him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.47,0:22:01.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you look at it that way, \Nhe didn't betray me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.35,0:22:05.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are the most amazing specimen, Shirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.90,0:22:09.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that Caster is an \Nenemy who must not run free,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.57,0:22:12.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but I believe Archer is not cruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.03,0:22:17.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on a second. What part of what \NI just said were you listening to?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.57,0:22:19.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You saw it, didn't you, Shirou?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.62,0:22:22.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,His technique was as pure as a clear stream.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.33,0:22:25.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,His heart must be equally as pure.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.42,0:22:30.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He's not that great with a sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.88,0:22:34.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The guy attacked me from behind, \Nbut he didn't manage to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.30,0:22:37.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you have an aptitude for it, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.18,0:22:42.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Given enough time and effort, \Nyou should be able to reach his level.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.98,0:22:46.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've made up my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.65,0:22:53.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Once I'm healed up, Saber, \Nteach me how to use a sword!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.57,0:22:56.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not just as exercise. How to really fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.53,0:22:59.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.45,0:23:00.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If that's what you want, Shirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.45,0:23:04.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That settles it, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.17,0:23:09.92,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't screw up again like I did tonight,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.92,0:23:11.99,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and running away at every \Nturn won't change anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.09,0:23:16.47,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And most of all, I can't let myself \Nlose to that bastard who said
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.47,0:23:21.14,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,he would sacrifice the lives of the \Nfew to save those of the many.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.38,0:23:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.89,0:23:27.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to smash that Bounded Field.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.56,0:23:29.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The enemy is planning to settle things here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.31,0:23:32.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make you pay for what \Nyou've done, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.73,0:23:34.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.19,0:23:37.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is how Servants ought to be!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.49,0:23:40.03,Next,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(552,1)}Next Time \NWinter Days, Where the Heart Is
